TTP Signal-Server JSON-stdout shim
===================================

SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-or-later
Upstream:  https://github.com/W3AXL/Signal-Server
Base SHA:  7f6242afb3685ff31d9ad14062b80d692ee56327 (master, 2025)
Purpose:   Add `-json` CLI flag that, in PPA mode, emits a single-line
           JSON document to stdout containing the computed path loss.
           This is a thin shim to bridge Signal-Server with the
           TELECOM-TOWER-POWER `signal_server_engine` adapter without
           altering any existing behaviour. Without `-json` the binary
           is byte-for-byte identical to upstream.

Validation status: PATCH WRITTEN AGAINST UPSTREAM SOURCE READ;
                   NOT YET BUILT LOCALLY (cmake unavailable in dev env).
                   Operator MUST verify `cmake ../src && make` succeeds
                   AND that `signalserver -json -lat ... -lon ... -rla
                   ... -rlo ... -txh ... -rxh ... -f ... -pm ... -sdf
                   <dir> -o <basename>` prints a JSON line as the LAST
                   line of stdout, before relying on it in production.

Apply with:  git apply scripts/signal_server_json.patch

